[XSUM]INTRODUCTION[XSUM]
A nine-year-old boy is being treated in hospital after being hit by a vehicle in North Lanarkshire on Saturday.

[XSUM]RESTBODY[XSUM]
Police said the boy was badly injured in the incident, after being struck in Coatbridge.
Emergency crews were called the scene on the town's Bank Street near Langloan Primary School at about 16:40.
The boy was taken to Queen Elizabeth University Hospital, in Glasgow, where his condition is believed to be serious.
